se you have further questions.\r\n\r\nThanks for your reply. I note that the shoot range and sight range are implemented in the `starcraft2.py` for source code of SMAC as follows:\r\n<img width=\"577\" alt=\"微信截图_20211112210400\" src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/45333787/141471903-3dc2fe90-15d6-48fd-9109-fd7125f9c7a4.png\">\r\n\r\nDoes it affect the game running if change them?","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/oxwhirl/smac/issues/comments/967111233/reactions","total_count":0,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"performed_via_github_app":null,"event":"commented","actor":{"login":"Duke-Allen","id":45333787,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjQ1MzMzNzg3","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/45333787?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/Duke-Allen","html_url":"https://github.com/Duke-Allen","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/Duke-Allen/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/Duke-Allen/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/Duke-Allen/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/Duke-Allen/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/Duke-Allen/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/Duke-Allen/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/Duke-Allen/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/Duke-Allen/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/Duke-Allen/received_events","type":"User","site_admin":false}},{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/oxwhirl/smac/issues/comments/967132938","html_url":"https://github.com/oxwhirl/smac/issues/85#issuecomment-967132938","issue_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/oxwhirl/smac/issues/85","id":967132938,"node_id":"IC_kwDOCdEVLM45pUcK","user":{"login":"samvelyan","id":9724413,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjk3MjQ0MTM=","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/9724413?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/samvelyan","html_url":"https://github.com/samvelyan","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/samvelyan/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/samvelyan/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/samvelyan/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/samvelyan/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/samvelyan/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/samvelyan/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/samvelyan/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/samvelyan/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/samvelyan/received_events","type":"User","site_admin":false},"created_at":"2021-11-12T13:51:13Z","updated_at":"2021-11-12T13:51:13Z","author_association":"COLLABORATOR","body":"Good question. These functions are only relevant for the RL agent, not the SC2 units.\r\n\r\nunit_sight_range() returns the distance that defines when our RL agents receive observations concerning other units of the game (although this number is different for certain SC2 units).\r\n\r\nunit_shoot_range() defines when the `attack` actions becomes available for the RL agents. Again, this can be different from the shooting range of actual SC2 units. If the unit_shoot_range() is larger than the attack range of a unit (e.g. Zealots), then the unit is ordered to go closer to the target and only then attacking (similar to how human players play with the mouse).\r\n\r\nI guess going back to you original question, it is **possible to modify these for the RL agent using SMAC**. Sorry about the confusion.\r\n\r\nI hope this makes sense. Let me know if you have further questions.","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/oxwhirl/smac/issues/comments/967132938/reactions","total_count":0,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"performed_via_github_app":null